      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/Knowledge\" title=\"Knowledge\">Knowledge</a> * <a href=\"/Endgame_Tablebases\" title=\"Endgame Tablebases\">Endgame Tablebases</a> * Scorpio Bitbases</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/File:Sco_bode.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7d/Sco_bode.jpg/330px-Sco_bode.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"287\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/7d/Sco_bode.jpg 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:Sco_bode.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scorpius\">Scorpio constellation</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div>\n<p><b>Scorpio Bitbases</b>,<br />\nare compact <a href=\"/Endgame_Bitbases\" title=\"Endgame Bitbases\">endgame bitbases</a> created by <a href=\"/Daniel_Shawul\" title=\"Daniel Shawul\">Daniel Shawul</a> with WDL information of up to 5-men, well suited to probe inside the <a href=\"/Search\" title=\"Search\">search</a> as applied in Daniel's engine <a href=\"/Scorpio\" title=\"Scorpio\">Scorpio</a>. The 5-men WDL holds in 200 MB. In order to make progress in won egtb-positions near the <a href=\"/Root\" title=\"Root\">root</a>, various <a href=\"/Evaluation\" title=\"Evaluation\">evaluation</a> heuristics are necessary to modify winning <a href=\"/Score\" title=\"Score\">scores</a> accordantly, considering <a href=\"/Material\" title=\"Material\">material</a>, ply-distance to the root, pawn closeness to promotion, <a href=\"/Distance\" title=\"Distance\">distance</a> of pieces to the opponent king, etc. <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> . \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Open_Source\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Open Source</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#2005_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2005 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#2010_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2010 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#2013\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2013</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#2014_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2014 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#2020_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2020 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Open_Source\">Open Source</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Scorpio_Bitbases&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Open Source\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>Scorpio Bitbases are open source, since October 2013 distributed under the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BSD_licenses\">BSD license</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> . Under <a href=\"/Windows\" title=\"Windows\">Windows</a>, probing is encapsulated via a <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dynamic-link_library\">Dynamic-link library</a>, which already provides a heuristic score instead of pure WDL information in order to make progress at the root without the need to probe huge DTC/DTM tablebases. As of January 2014, Daniel finished the <b>6-men</b> Scorpio Bitbases, available from <a href=\"/index.php?title=Joshua_Shriver&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Joshua Shriver (page does not exist)\">Joshua Shriver's</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BitTorrent\">torrent</a> site <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>. \n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Scorpio_Bitbases&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/Endgame_Bitbases\" title=\"Endgame Bitbases\">Bitbases</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Edwards%27_Tablebases\" title=\"Edwards&#39; Tablebases\">Edwards' Tablebases</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Gaviota_Tablebases\" title=\"Gaviota Tablebases\">Gaviota Tablebases</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Felicity_Tablebases\" title=\"Felicity Tablebases\">Felicity Tablebases</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Lomonosov_Tablebases\" title=\"Lomonosov Tablebases\">Lomonosov Tablebases</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Nalimov_Tablebases\" title=\"Nalimov Tablebases\">Nalimov Tablebases</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Scorpio\" title=\"Scorpio\">Scorpio</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Syzygy_Bases\" title=\"Syzygy Bases\">Syzygy Bases</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Thompson%27s_Databases\" title=\"Thompson&#39;s Databases\">Thompson's Databases</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Scorpio_Bitbases&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2005_...\">2005 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Scorpio_Bitbases&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: 2005 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=467250\">Bitbases - yace, scorpio, gambitfruit</a> by <a href=\"/index.php?title=Bernhard_Bauer&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Bernhard Bauer (page does not exist)\">Bernhard Bauer</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, December 06, 2005</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?topic_view=threads&amp;p=111335&amp;t=12987\">Re: Open Source bitbase program</a> by <a href=\"/Daniel_Shawul\" title=\"Daniel Shawul\">Daniel Shawul</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 12, 2007</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=19240\">Scorpio BBs, licenses</a> by <a href=\"/Zach_Wegner\" title=\"Zach Wegner\">Zach Wegner</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 28, 2008</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.open-aurec.com/wbforum/viewtopic.php?f=4&amp;t=7119\">Scorpio bitbases</a> by <a href=\"/index.php?title=Manuel_Pe%C3%B1a&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Manuel Peña (page does not exist)\">Manuel Peña</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Winboard Forum</a>, February 07, 2008</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=25211\">Scorpio endgame bitbase specs?</a> by <a href=\"/Ilari_Pihlajisto\" title=\"Ilari Pihlajisto\">Ilari Pihlajisto</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, December 02, 2008</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=26936\">New Scorpio bitbase files</a> by <a href=\"/Dann_Corbit\" title=\"Dann Corbit\">Dann Corbit</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, March 09, 2009</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=27339\">Scorpio bitbases</a> by <a href=\"/Matthias_Gemuh\" title=\"Matthias Gemuh\">Matthias Gemuh</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 06, 2009</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=27642\">Scorpio bitbases with linux. Any success?</a> by <a href=\"/Joona_Kiiski\" title=\"Joona Kiiski\">Joona Kiiski</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 29, 2009</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=29853\">EGBB implementation</a> by <a href=\"/Michael_Hoffmann\" title=\"Michael Hoffmann\">Michael Hoffmann</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, September 24, 2009</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2010_...\">2010 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Scorpio_Bitbases&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: 2010 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.open-chess.org/viewtopic.php?f=3&amp;t=778\">Some tablebase formats</a> by <a href=\"/Mark_Watkins\" title=\"Mark Watkins\">BB+</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">OpenChess Forum</a>, November 25, 2010</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=43872\">bitbase access by Scorpio versions... Dan Shawul?</a> by <a href=\"/index.php?title=Ernest_Bonnem&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Ernest Bonnem (page does not exist)\">Ernest Bonnem</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, May 28, 2012</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=44553\">pawn enumeration</a> by <a href=\"/Daniel_Shawul\" title=\"Daniel Shawul\">Daniel Shawul</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, July 24, 2012</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=45009&amp;start=4\">Re: Search with bitbase</a> by <a href=\"/Daniel_Shawul\" title=\"Daniel Shawul\">Daniel Shawul</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, September 05, 2012</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=45608\">Houdini 3 with Scorpio Bitbases Question</a> by Milton Zucker, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 16, 2012</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2013\">2013</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Scorpio_Bitbases&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: 2013\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=49572&amp;start=1\">Re: syzygy question (for Ronald)</a> by <a href=\"/Daniel_Shawul\" title=\"Daniel Shawul\">Daniel Shawul</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 04, 2013</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=49615\">Scorpio Egbb Thread</a> by <a href=\"/index.php?title=Joshua_Shriver&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Joshua Shriver (page does not exist)\">Joshua Shriver</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 07, 2013</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=49684\">What happens using egbb</a> by <a href=\"/Kai_Laskos\" title=\"Kai Laskos\">Kai Laskos</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 12, 2013</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://rybkaforum.net/cgi-bin/rybkaforum/topic_show.pl?tid=27837\">Scorpio E.G.T.B.</a> by AxeFever, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Rybka Forum</a>, October 22, 2013</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=49819\">Syzygy / egbb discussion</a> by <a href=\"/Daniel_Shawul\" title=\"Daniel Shawul\">Daniel Shawul</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 23, 2013&#160;» <a href=\"/Syzygy_Bases\" title=\"Syzygy Bases\">Syzygy Bases</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=50633\">Scorpio bitbases question</a> by <a href=\"/Harm_Geert_Muller\" title=\"Harm Geert Muller\">Harm Geert Muller</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, December 25, 2013</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2014_...\">2014 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Scorpio_Bitbases&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: 2014 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=50894\">Scorpio 6men EGBB Now available</a> by <a href=\"/index.php?title=Joshua_Shriver&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Joshua Shriver (page does not exist)\">Joshua Shriver</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 14, 2014</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.open-chess.org/viewtopic.php?f=3&amp;t=2568\">50 Gb 6-men scorpio bitbases available</a> by <a href=\"/Daniel_Shawul\" title=\"Daniel Shawul\">stackOVERFLOW</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">OpenChess Forum</a>, January 14, 2014</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=51096\">Stockfish goes EGBB</a> by <a href=\"/Daniel_Shawul\" title=\"Daniel Shawul\">Daniel Shawul</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 29, 2014&#160;» <a href=\"/Stockfish\" title=\"Stockfish\">Stockfish</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=51133\">Scorpio &amp; egbb issue (OSX)</a> by Max May, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 01, 2014&#160;» <a href=\"/KBNK_Endgame\" title=\"KBNK Endgame\">KBNK Endgame</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=51159\">Performance of Syzygy and Scorpio</a> by <a href=\"/Kai_Laskos\" title=\"Kai Laskos\">Kai Laskos</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 04, 2014&#160;» <a href=\"/Syzygy_Bases\" title=\"Syzygy Bases\">Syzygy Bases</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=66804\">Problem position using Scorpio Egbbs</a> by <a href=\"/Ross_Boyd\" title=\"Ross Boyd\">Ross Boyd</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, March 11, 2018</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=67600\">Egbb dll neural network support</a> by <a href=\"/Daniel_Shawul\" title=\"Daniel Shawul\">Daniel Shawul</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, May 29, 2018&#160;» <a href=\"/Neural_Networks\" title=\"Neural Networks\">Neural Networks</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2020_...\">2020 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Scorpio_Bitbases&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: 2020 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=75400&amp;start=22\">Re: Hacking around CFish NNUE</a> by <a href=\"/Daniel_Shawul\" title=\"Daniel Shawul\">Daniel Shawul</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 15, 2020&#160;» <a href=\"/NNUE\" title=\"NNUE\">NNUE</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=75415&amp;start=3\">Re: How to scale stockfish NNUE score?</a> by <a href=\"/Daniel_Shawul\" title=\"Daniel Shawul\">Daniel Shawul</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 17, 2020&#160;» <a href=\"/Stockfish_NNUE\" title=\"Stockfish NNUE\">Stockfish NNUE</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=75803\">EGBB (endgame bitbases) questions ...</a>  by <a href=\"/Frank_Quisinsky\" title=\"Frank Quisinsky\">Frank Quisinsky</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, November 15, 2020</li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Scorpio_Bitbases&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://sites.google.com/site/dshawul/\">Scorpio Chess and Nebiyu Alien</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/dshawul/egbbdll\">dshawul/egbbdll · GitHub</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/dshawul/Scorpio\">dshawul/Scorpio · GitHub</a> includes Six men egbb code</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://oics.olympuschess.com/tracker/index.php\">OICS Chess and EGTB Tracker Statistics</a> by <a href=\"/index.php?title=Joshua_Shriver&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Joshua Shriver (page does not exist)\">Joshua Shriver</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://chess.cygnitec.com/tablebases/scorpio/\">Index of /tablebases/scorpio</a> by <a href=\"/Franklin_Titus\" title=\"Franklin Titus\">kingliveson</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Scorpio_Bitbases&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scorpius\">Scorpio constellation</a> 1782, from <a href=\"/Mathematician#JEBode\" title=\"Mathematician\">Bode's</a> revised and enlarged edition of <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.astrobril.nl/Fortin76.html\">Fortin's small star atlas</a> of <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Flamsteed\">Flamsteed</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=45009&amp;start=4\">Re: Search with bitbase</a> by <a href=\"/Daniel_Shawul\" title=\"Daniel Shawul\">Daniel Shawul</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, September 05, 2012</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=49572&amp;start=7\">Added liscense</a> by <a href=\"/Daniel_Shawul\" title=\"Daniel Shawul\">Daniel Shawul</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 04, 2013</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=50894\">Scorpio 6men EGBB Now available</a> by <a href=\"/index.php?title=Joshua_Shriver&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Joshua Shriver (page does not exist)\">Joshua Shriver</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 14, 2014</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/dshawul/Scorpio\">dshawul/Scorpio · GitHub</a> includes Six men egbb code</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BitTorrent\">BitTorrent from Wikipedia</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<p><b><a href=\"/Endgame_Tablebases\" title